name: Neeeerd
notes: 0§0§0§0§<:rare_ml:769348056918392832>:nerd:<:rare_r:769348056763990087>§You see, time travel is possible however it's quite difficult. First you need to find a way to withstand the gravitational forces of a black hole. But not any any hole, a spinning one. You see, what happens is, when a black hole spins, the singularity at the center becomes in infinitly thin torus instead of an infinitly small point. If a space craft were to pass through that torus, it would be prepelled into a parrallel universe. Unfortunatly, it would be impossible to return to the original universe because if you were to go through the torus again, you enter another parrallel univers. Essentialy you'd never return to the original universe.
